---
import PageLayout from '../layouts/PageLayout.astro';
---

<PageLayout
  title="About Me"
  description="Software Engineer student at URJC, originally from Murcia. Seeking internship for Summer 2026."
  eyebrow="About"
>
  <section class="content-shell py-12 space-y-12">

    <div class="space-y-3 max-w-3xl">
      <p class="m-0 text-ink text-2xl font-semibold leading-tight">
        I am a Software Engineer who believes that great technology is built on trust, discipline, and a global perspective.
      </p>
      <p class="m-0 text-muted">
        Originally from Murcia, Spain, I carry the energy of the sun and the Mediterranean in my approach to life and work. I am a Double Degree student in Computer Science and Software Engineering at Universidad Rey Juan Carlos, driven by a "learning by doing" mindset and a deep-seated desire to use my knowledge to empower those around me.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="space-y-3 max-w-3xl">
      <h2 class="text-sm font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-ink m-0"> A Global Perspective</h2>
      <p class="m-0 text-muted">
        I don't just build software; I seek to understand the world it lives in. My journey has taken me from an academic year in Argentina (UADE) to volunteering in the jungles of Costa Rica. I am a traveler at heart, always eager to experience new cultures, religions, and flavors. I believe that being a great engineer requires the empathy and open-mindedness that only comes from seeing the world.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="space-y-3 max-w-3xl">
      <h2 class="text-sm font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-ink m-0"> Commitment & Loyalty</h2>
      <p class="m-0 text-muted">
        In both my personal life and my professional projects, I value depth. While I am naturally cautious when building new bonds, once trust is established, I am entirely devoted to my circle and my craft. This translates into my work: when I commit to a project—like developing the Mar y Bosque ERP or digitalizing local businesses—I give it my all, ensuring the solution is robust and truly helpful for the community.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="space-y-3 max-w-3xl">
      <h2 class="text-sm font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-ink m-0"> Technical Grit & Continuous Growth</h2>
      <p class="m-0 text-muted">I am currently refining my stack with a focus on high-impact tools:</p>
      <ul class="m-0 text-muted space-y-1 list-none pl-0">
        <li><span class="text-ink font-semibold">Modern Web —</span> Deep-diving into React and Node.js (Helsinki's Full Stack Open) and Harvard's CS50W.</li>
        <li><span class="text-ink font-semibold">Systems —</span> Mastering Docker and microservices to build scalable, reliable infrastructure.</li>
        <li><span class="text-ink font-semibold">Algorithm Mastery —</span> Training with NeetCode and preparing for the AWS Cloud Practitioner certification.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="space-y-3 max-w-3xl">
      <h2 class="text-sm font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-ink m-0"> The Goal</h2>
      <p class="m-0 text-muted">
        I have a very clear vision for my future. I am seeking a <span class="text-ink font-semibold">Software Engineering Internship for Summer 2026</span>, ready to relocate to Lisbon, London, Amsterdam, or Berlin.
      </p>
      <p class="m-0 text-muted">
        Beyond the terminal, you'll find me recharging under the sun, at the beach, or enjoying the company of my close friends. My life is soundtracked by the soul of Flamenco (Parrita, Jeros, El Barrio) and the rhythm of Salsa — disciplines that, like engineering, require both heart and precision.
      </p>
    </div>

  </section>
</PageLayout>